Everton, Bolton Rally to Win in Carling Cup Soccer; West Ham Eliminated

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-08-24T21:57:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/everton-bolton-rally-to-win-in-carling-cup-soccer-west-ham-eliminated.html
Premier League clubs Everton and
Bolton rallied to win at home against lower-division teams in
the second round of English soccer’s League Cup.  Tuncay Sanli and  Martin Petrov  scored in the second half as
Bolton beat Macclesfield of the fourth-tier League Two 2-1,
while Everton defeated League One’s Sheffield United 3-1.  West Ham and Bristol City of the second-tier Championship
both lost at home to League Two clubs in first-round matches.
West Ham fell 2-1 to Aldershot and Bristol City lost 1-0 to
Swindon.  In other second round games, Premier League clubs Liverpool
and Blackburn were 3-1 winners over Exeter City and Sheffield
Wednesday, respectively, while Middlesbrough won 2-0 at
Peterborough.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in  London  at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
